cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MA, cs.SY, cs.PF

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on investigating the cumulative distribution function of the aggregate interference in CSMA/CA networks, which is a networking protocol. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the channel model and analyzes the power distribution, which are related to information theory. 
3. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) - The paper assumes that nodes are deployed in an infinite two-dimensional plane by Poisson point process, which is a common technique used in multiagent systems. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper analyzes the dynamics of the distributed coordinate function in a common sensing area, which is related to systems and control. 
5. cs.PF (Performance) - The paper evaluates the performance of the CSMA/CA protocol by analyzing the CDF of the aggregate interference, which is related to performance evaluation.
